00:36:47,839 --> 00:36:50,900
I didn't mean to take things
so far in front of Andrews.

512
00:36:50,975 --> 00:36:53,069
I guess I had a
tiny overreaction.

513
00:36:54,312 --> 00:36:57,476
It's okay for us to be nice
to each other... sometimes.

514
00:37:01,519 --> 00:37:02,519
Headed home?

515
00:37:04,089 --> 00:37:06,820
I wouldn't mind some
company if you're up for it.

516
00:37:08,460 --> 00:37:10,759
See? Nice is good.

517
00:37:14,199 --> 00:37:15,199
Sometimes.

518
00:37:15,934 --> 00:37:17,197
I'll see you at your place.

519
00:37:35,220 --> 00:37:36,220
Where's Leo?

520
00:37:38,022 --> 00:37:39,285
I don't know.

521
00:37:41,059 --> 00:37:42,994
I asked him if this
could be enough.

522
00:37:44,395 --> 00:37:45,556
If I could be...

523
00:37:48,099 --> 00:37:50,898
He loves me, I knew that,

524
00:37:51,870 --> 00:37:54,101
but not enough.

525
00:37:57,542 --> 00:37:59,204
I suppose I knew that too.

526
00:38:02,280 --> 00:38:03,578
As long as he was here,

527
00:38:04,783 --> 00:38:06,581
I would never make
room for anyone else...

528
00:38:08,620 --> 00:38:10,054
so I asked him to go.

529
00:38:19,931 --> 00:38:21,092
I'm sorry.

530
00:38:21,833 --> 00:38:22,833
It's okay.

531
00:38:23,935 --> 00:38:26,097
I'm sure there are
a ton of great guys

532
00:38:26,171 --> 00:38:29,039
